args: I cooked you a meal, my darling!\nIt would make me so happy if you ate it!

Oh, um...my thanks. However, I regret to
admit that I'm currently quite stuffed.
Yes, completely full up to the gills,
I'm afraid.
Oh, and I'm in a bit of a hurry as well,\nso I must be going. Ta!
Sweetie-muffs, that band of minstrels\nyou love is coming to town! I thought\nperhaps we might go together?
Er, well, I'm delighted that you would\nask, but I fear have some...business\nto attend to. Yes, that's it. Apologies.
Oooh honey buuuun! Let's you and I\nspend the day together in blissfu—
Not a problem. You look like you've been\nthrough the wringer.
Do women always pursue you so...\naggressively?
I fear the fault is mine.
If I could simply respond to them honestly,\nI wouldn't find myself in this situation.
Well, I do think you don't really need to\nrun away like that...
Haaaaaa...ha. Yes, quite. Normally, there\nwould be no need to do that.

{player_name}, might you lend
an ear to my sad tale?
It would do me good to
tell it to a friend.
...I once had a fiancée, you see.
I loved her more than life itself, and she\nfelt the same in return. ...Or so I thought.
My family's trading business fell upon\nhard times.
It's no stretch to say that I was at risk\nof being utterly ruined.
And in the midst of all that...
No, it is not over. I can dig my way out\nof this. I know there is a way!
So long as I have you, my love,\nthere is nothing I cannot do.
You don't understand, Naveed.\nIt's over for ME.
I have decided to marry another.
A man who would allow himself to fall\ninto ruin is not a man I wish to marry.
But...but what of our feelings? Our love?\nWas it all a lie?
No, it is real. ...Or it was, once.
But even the strongest love can wither and\ndie on the vine.
How can you say such a thing? True love\nis stronger than any crisis!
Then please feel free to search for this\n＂true love＂ with another.
...Ever since, I've struggled with even the\nthought of a woman showing me affection.
All I can think about is the chance I might\nbe betrayed yet again.
Going through an experience like that\nwould indeed make it difficult to trust\nsomeone again. However, I think—
Save your words, Prince! I know you will\nattempt to convince me that not all women\nwould behave in the same manner.
And yes, my head knows that to be true.
But my heart... Well, it seems to believe\nsomething else entirely.
Love is but a crystal sword—it seems\nstrong and pure, yet it can shatter at the\nslightest touch!
I don't think you actually believe love is as\nfragile as all that.
If you did, you wouldn't be so conflicted\nabout it.
It is as you say: I DO want to believe in\nlove.
I want to believe that somewhere out there\nis a true love that does not waver when\ntimes are hard.
In fact, it is my search for true love that\nhas driven my journey to this point.
Or I believe it does, at any rate.
It makes sense that you would think as\nmuch. There are many here with big,\nstrong hearts—including you.
And being around such hearts makes\nme feel as if I'm getting closer to\nunderstanding what true love is.
If I could decipher that, perhaps I would\nno longer feel the need to flee affection.
I hope he finds what he's looking for...
